{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Check Secrets Manager Before Giving Up",
  "description": "When the agent is about to stop execution (give up, say it cannot do something, or report a permission/auth failure), first check AWS Secrets Manager for any relevant API keys or tokens that could resolve the issue. Available secrets include: seraphim/github-token, seraphim/anthropic, seraphim/openai, seraphim/stripe, seraphim/telegram, seraphim/youtube, seraphim/kalshi, seraphim/discord, seraphim/x, seraphim/instagram, seraphim/heygen, seraphim/zeely, seraphim/reddit, seraphim/googleplay, and SeraphimAuroraSecret.",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "agentStop"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "BEFORE saying you cannot do something or giving up due to missing credentials/tokens/API keys:\n\n1. Check AWS Secrets Manager for the needed credential:\n   aws secretsmanager get-secret-value --secret-id \"seraphim/<service-name>\" --region us-east-1 --query \"SecretString\" --output text\n\n2. Available secrets in Secrets Manager:\n   - seraphim/github-token (GitHub PAT for zionxai5000)\n   - seraphim/anthropic (Anthropic API key)\n   - seraphim/openai (OpenAI API key)\n   - seraphim/stripe (Stripe API key)\n   - seraphim/telegram (Telegram bot token)\n   - seraphim/youtube (YouTube API credentials)\n   - seraphim/kalshi (Kalshi API key)\n   - seraphim/discord (Discord bot token)\n   - seraphim/x (X/Twitter API key)\n   - seraphim/instagram (Instagram API)\n   - seraphim/heygen (HeyGen API key)\n   - seraphim/zeely (Zeely API key)\n   - seraphim/reddit (Reddit API)\n   - seraphim/googleplay (Google Play credentials)\n   - SeraphimAuroraSecret3FC3811-bVxbXGVUFH2L (Aurora PostgreSQL credentials)\n\n3. If the task requires authentication to ANY external service, retrieve the credential from Secrets Manager FIRST before reporting failure.\n\n4. For git operations specifically: use seraphim/github-token with the remote URL format:\n   https://zionxai5000:<TOKEN>@github.com/zionxai5000/<repo>.git\n\nNEVER say \"I don't have access\" or \"permission denied\" without first checking Secrets Manager."
  }
}